My answer would, it wouldn't.  But I don't think that is a valid argment though.  let me ask you this.  Were Warriors to get Mend, would that adversely effect you?  Well we ought to have it cuz we have the most hit points and have the most need for it to help our down time and to help us from getting mauled by greens.  Or how about this, Why can't warriors get Feign Death?  Rogues get evade for lowering agro, Monks get Feign Death for lowering agro, Pallys and SK also have ways to help them avoid dying.  Warriors are SOL.  If we had FD would it adversely effect you?  How?   It all comes down to what many others have said.  Verant has designed the game the way it is for a reason.  Its called &quot;balance&quot;.  Yes you having Invis doesn't hurt anyone else's game but it makes you more &quot;independent&quot; and thus have to rely on other classes less.  They want us to group and they have designed the game in such a way that some classes can do some thing and others can do other things.  Not one class can do everything.  Clerics can't invis.  /shrug  Thats the way it is. <p><div align="left">
